Is this still irreducible wherever it now is?
I think we prefer the `irreducible` tag now and then we can use `unseal`/`with_unfolding_all` to access the internals.

I am not sure if it makes a difference but you can also specify `nsmul_zero := fun _ => by with_unfolding_all rfl` and not unseal `nsmul` in all of the declaration. Unsealing something in a situation where you are building data makes me nervous. I think it is ok here but better to default to the latter. Also below.
